50 First Dates;;2004;;PG-13;;Comedy,Drama,Romance;;6.8;;Peter Segal;;Adam Sandler,Drew Barrymore,Rob Schneider,Sean Astin,Lusia Strus,Dan Aykroyd,Amy Hill,Allen Covert,Blake Clark,Maya Rudolph,Pomaika'i Brown,Joe Nakashima,Peter Dante,Dom Magwili,Jonathan Loughran,J.D. Donaruma,Wayne Federman,Kent Avenido;;Henry Roth (Adam Sandler) is a wildlife veterinarian in Hawaii, who meets Lucy Whitmore (Drew Barrymore) a woman who has a short-term memory loss from an auto accident a year earlier. Henry is a ladies man on the island who has been breaking the hearts of female tourists for years. Henry meets Lucy at a local cafe and takes her out on a date. Henry falls in love with Lucy, but there is one problem when she awakens in the morning, she can't remember him or anything that happened that day. Henry must devise a plan to meet Lucy everyday and try to get her to fall in love with him again and again. Douglas Young (the-movie-guy);;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0343660/